The paper deals with the interpretation of black-box models, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of deep convolutional neural networks for image classification suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also proposes a model-agnostic method, which is relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The use of probabilistic sound methodology suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also discusses the saturation phenomenon of classifiers, which is relevant to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Finally, the application of the method to commercial general vision recognition systems suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
